[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man dies in light aircraft crash in Wiltshire

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man died after a light aircraft crashed near an airfield in Wiltshire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Wiltshire Police confirmed the man died at the scene after the plane came down in a field close to Dinton, near Salisbury, at about 10:50 BST.
Another man was rescued from the wreckage and taken to hospital in Salisbury.
The Air Accidents Investigation Branch confirmed it will be conducting an investigation into the crash.
Wiltshire Police said the dead man's next of kin have been informed and its "thoughts remain with the families of those involved at this difficult time".
